{"cursor":"6677","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"'The Establishment' is a term used to refer to a visible dominant group or elite\nthat holds power or authority in a nation or organization. The term suggests a\nclosed social group which selects its own members (as opposed to selection by\ninheritance, merit or election). The term can be used to describe specific\nentrenched elite structures in specific institutions, but is usually informal in\napplication and is more likely used by the media than by scholars.\n","linknr":180,"url":"The_Establishment","recorded":1362562767,"links":26,"instances":["philosophy","hong_kong"],"pdf":[],"categories":["Sociolinguistics","Social groups","Political terminology","Oligarchy","Politics of the United Kingdom"],"headings":["Pakistan","United Kingdom","American Sociological Association","Hong Kong","See also","References","Further reading"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/3b/Text_document_with_page_number_icon.svg/40px-Text_document_with_page_number_icon.svg.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/18/Nuvola_kdict_glass.svg/40px-Nuvola_kdict_glass.svg.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/vector/images/search-ltr.png?303-4","//bits.wikimedia.org/images/wikimedia-button.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/poweredby_mediawiki_88x31.png"],"tags":[["power","philosophy"],["legislative_council","hong_kong"]],"members":["power","legislative_council"],"related":["Elite","Power_(philosophy)","Authority","Nation","United_Kingdom","Civil_servant","Aristocracy","Church_of_England","BBC","British_monarchy","Henry_Fairlie","Henry_Fairlie","Ralph_Waldo_Emerson","Loanword","Sociology","American_Sociological_Association","Hong_Kong_politics","Chinese_Communist_Party","Transfer_of_sovereignty_over_Hong_Kong","Hong_Kong_Government","Pro-democracy_camp","Cantonese_language","Chinese_character","Royalist","Communism","Derogatory","Legislative_Council_(Ho